answer.p:
3. In this situation, A is diagonalizable if and only if the 3-eigenspace is a plane. For example, the matrix


                        \mat{
                        3 1 0;
                        0 3 0;
                        0 0 5
                        }
                        \text{is not diagonalizable, but}
                        \mat{
                        3 0 0;
                        0 3 0;
                        0 0 5
                        }
                        \text{is.}
